    faqs: [
      { question: 'How much does it cost to hire an AI developer in India in 2026?', answer: 'Senior AI developers: $55-$90/hour ($5,500-$9,000/month on retainer). Mid-level: $30-$55/hour. ML/research specialists: $80-$150/hour. A typical AI feature costs $3,000-$8,000 (RAG) to $15,000-$30,000 (full agentic MVP) — roughly 60-75% less than equivalent US rates.' },
      { question: 'Are Indian AI developers as good as US AI developers?', answer: 'For applied LLM work (API integrations, RAG, agents, production systems), yes, at the senior tier. For cutting-edge ML research, the US still leads thanks to top research labs and academia. 90% of AI projects are applied work — so for most founders, the answer is yes.' },
      { question: 'Can I hire an Indian AI developer for a fixed price?', answer: 'Yes. For scoped projects (chatbot, RAG system, AI feature), fixed-price is the standard. For open-ended research or unknowns, hourly or weekly retainers are fairer to both sides. Milestone payments (40/30/30) protect both parties.' },
      { question: 'What tools do Indian AI developers use in 2026?', answer: 'Claude, OpenAI, Gemini, Llama 3.x, Mistral, direct SDK calls (LangChain only for prototypes), Pinecone/pgvector/Qdrant, Next.js, FastAPI, Python, TypeScript, Supabase, Braintrust/LangSmith for evaluation. Stack is the same as the US.' },
      { question: 'How do I pay an AI developer in India?', answer: 'Wise (0.5-1% fees, 1-2 days) for milestone payments. Stripe (2.9% + 30¢, instant) for retainer subscriptions. USD wire for single large payments ($15-$40 flat). Avoid PayPal (4-7% fees). Pay in USD — conversion is the developer\'s problem.' },
      { question: 'How long does it take to hire an AI developer in India?', answer: 'With a clear brief and high-signal sourcing, 10-14 days from first outreach to signed SOW and kickoff call. Skipping the paid test task shortens to 5 days but roughly doubles the risk of a bad hire.' },
      { question: 'Should I hire a freelancer or an AI-focused agency in India?', answer: 'For projects under $25,000, always a senior freelancer. For $25,000-$75,000, it depends — freelancer if scope is clear, agency if you need PM/QA/design layered in. Above $75,000, agency or a managed hybrid team wins.' },
    ],
